{
  "page": "Utherydes Wayn",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Wayn\" title=\"House Wayn\"><img alt=\"House Wayn.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/56/House_Wayn.svg/50px-House_Wayn.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/56/House_Wayn.svg/75px-House_Wayn.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/56/House_Wayn.svg/100px-House_Wayn.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Utherydes Wayn</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Wayn\" title=\"House Wayn\"><img alt=\"House Wayn.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/56/House_Wayn.svg/50px-House_Wayn.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/56/House_Wayn.svg/75px-House_Wayn.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/56/House_Wayn.svg/100px-House_Wayn.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\nSteward of <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Wayn\" title=\"House Wayn\">House Wayn</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Tully\" title=\"House Tully\">House Tully</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Rivermen\" title=\"Rivermen\">Rivermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_238_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">238</a>–<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_240_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">240&#160;AC</a> (roughly)<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">Riverlands</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafutherydes_wayn.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafutherydes_wayn.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (appendix)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (appendix)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Utherydes Wayn</b> is the steward of <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a> under Lords <a href=\"/index.php/Hoster_Tully\" title=\"Hoster Tully\">Hoster</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Edmure_Tully\" title=\"Edmure Tully\">Edmure Tully</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragotappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragotappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Character_and_Appearance\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Character and Appearance</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes_by_Utherydes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes by Utherydes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Quotes_about_Utherydes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes about Utherydes</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Character_and_Appearance\">Character and Appearance</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Utherydes_Wayn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Character and Appearance\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Utherydes is an old man.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> He is grave, gaunt and sour.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_events\">Recent events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Utherydes_Wayn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Utherydes_Wayn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Utherydes informs Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a> on her arrival at <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a> that Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Hoster_Tully\" title=\"Hoster Tully\">Hoster Tully</a> is bedridden and has instructed him to bring his daughter to his bedside at once. Looking at him, Catelyn is surprised how old and grey her father's steward has become.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Utherydes_Wayn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Utherydes accompanies Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Edmure_Tully\" title=\"Edmure Tully\">Edmure Tully</a> when he greets his sister Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a> upon her arrival at <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a> after her mission to secure an alliance with <a href=\"/index.php/Renly_Baratheon\" title=\"Renly Baratheon\">Renly Baratheon</a> has failed because of his untimely death. When she sees Utherydes and the other men at Ser Edmure's side, Catelyn realizes that they are all of her father's age, old men who spent their lives in the service of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Hoster_Tully\" title=\"Hoster Tully\">Hoster Tully</a>. The men are introduced to <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a> by Catelyn. Utheryds inquires about the possibility of an alliance with <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a> as Stannis' letter about the illegitimacy of Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a>'s children has forestalled any possibility of him allying with the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">Lannisters</a>, but Catelyn, wary of Stannis because of the dark circumstances of Renly's death, dodges the question. He informs her that her son <a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb Stark</a> has left orders to send his lady mother to the <a href=\"/index.php/Twins\" title=\"Twins\">Twins</a> upon her return, so that she can select a bride for Robb from among Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Walder_Frey\" title=\"Walder Frey\">Walder Frey</a>'s daughters. However, Catelyn has no intention of doing that and wants to stay at Riverrun. Utherydes later informs her that, when Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Cleos_Frey\" title=\"Cleos Frey\">Cleos Frey</a> returned as envoy from <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>, he brought along the remains of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a>, as demanded in Robb's initial peace offer. When Catelyn has a look at the bones, she notices that the <a href=\"/index.php/Longsword\" title=\"Longsword\">longsword</a> that has been put in the hands of the skeleton is not the <a href=\"/index.php/Greatsword\" title=\"Greatsword\">greatsword</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Ice\" title=\"Ice\">Ice</a>. Utherydes informs her that her husband's sword has not been returned, only Lord Eddard's bones. Catelyn says that she'd have to thank Queen Cersei for even that much, receiving the answer by Utherydes that <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> in fact arranged for the return of the remains. Catelyn then commands Utherydes to arrange for her husband's remains to be transported to <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a>, escorted by <a href=\"/index.php/Hallis_Mollen\" title=\"Hallis Mollen\">Hallis Mollen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>While waiting for the outcome of the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Fords\" title=\"Battle of the Fords\">Battle of the Fords</a> that goes on around Riverrun, Lady Catelyn commands Utherydes to provide Ser Cleos Frey with a flagon of <a href=\"/index.php/Wine\" title=\"Wine\">wine</a>, as she wants to loosen his tongue before questioning him about the peace terms sent by Tyrion Lannister.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Utherydes_Wayn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>After Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a> has organized the escape of Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a>, it falls upon <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a>'s castellan Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Desmond_Grell\" title=\"Desmond Grell\">Desmond Grell</a> to confine her until her son <a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb Stark</a> decides what to do with her. Because he feels uneasy about the task of making Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Hoster_Tully\" title=\"Hoster Tully\">Hoster Tully</a>'s daughter a de-facto prisoner, Ser Desmond brings Utherydes along when he talks to Catelyn. Utherydes is grave during the whole encounter. He assures Catelyn that all of Riverrun shares her grief about the supposed deaths of her sons <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Rickon_Stark\" title=\"Rickon Stark\">Rickon Stark</a> but suggests that this does not justify her actions. Utherydes proposes that Catelyn should be confined to her own chambers, but she asks that it be her father's chambers instead so that she can tend to him, which is granted to her. Utherydes tells her that what she did was grave and that it has all been for naught, as the Kingslayer is being pursued by Riverrun's captain of the guards, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Robin_Ryger\" title=\"Robin Ryger\">Robin Ryger</a>. Catelyn notices that Utherydes has sad eyes while he talks with her.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When Lady Catelyn questions Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Vyman\" title=\"Vyman\">Vyman</a> whether he knows anyone called <a href=\"/index.php/Tansy_(plant)\" title=\"Tansy (plant)\">Tansy</a>, a name her delirious father has mentioned, the maester negates but suggests to ask Utherydes, as the steward would surely know if a person of that name has ever served at Riverrun. Maester Vyman later tells Catelyn that he has checked with Utherydes and that the steward is certain that such a person has not been employed under his watch.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>He announces Lady Catelyn's presence when Ser Desmond escorts her to her son Robb during a reception after his return to Riverrun. He also later signals the end of the meeting, when Robb asks him to do so. Robb later advises his wife <a href=\"/index.php/Jeyne_Westerling\" title=\"Jeyne Westerling\">Jeyne Westerling</a> and her mother <a href=\"/index.php/Sybell_Spicer\" title=\"Sybell Spicer\">Sybell Spicer</a> that Utherydes will find accomodations for them and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Edmure_Tully\" title=\"Edmure Tully\">Edmure Tully</a> offers to escort them to him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Utherydes_Wayn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_by_Utherydes\">Quotes by Utherydes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Utherydes_Wayn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes by Utherydes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Can we hope for no help from the south, Lady <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\">Stark</a>? This charge of <a href=\"/index.php/Incest\" title=\"Incest\">incest</a> &#8230; Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin</a> does not suffer such slights lightly. He will seek to wash the stain from his <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">daughter's</a> name with the blood of her accuser. Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis</a> must see that. He has no choice but to make common cause with us.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Utherydes to <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Catelyn</b>: <i><a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Ned</a>?</i><br /><b>Utherydes</b>: Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Cleos_Frey\" title=\"Cleos Frey\">Cleos</a> brought him from <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>, my lady.<br /><b>Catelyn</b>: Take me to him. I would look on him.<br /><b>Utherydes</b>: Only the ones remain, my lady.<br /><b>Catelyn</b>: I would look on him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Utherydes and <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>We share you grief, my lady. All <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a> mourns with you, but &#8230;<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Utherydes to <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>It was a grave thing you did, my lady, but for naught. Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Desmond_Grell\" title=\"Desmond Grell\">Desmond</a> has sent Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Robin_Ryger\" title=\"Robin Ryger\">Robin Ryger</a> after them, to bring back <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Kingslayer</a> &#8230; or failing that, his head.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Utherydes to <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_about_Utherydes\">Quotes about Utherydes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Utherydes_Wayn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes about Utherydes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>They have given their lives to <a href=\"/index.php/Hoster_Tully\" title=\"Hoster Tully\">my father's</a> service, and I have repaid them with disgrace.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a> on Utherydes and <a href=\"/index.php/Desmond_Grell\" title=\"Desmond Grell\">Desmond Grell</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>I spoke to Utherydes Wayn, my lady. He is quite certain that no woman by the name of <a href=\"/index.php/Tansy_(plant)\" title=\"Tansy (plant)\">Tansy</a> has ever been at <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a> during his service.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Vyman\" title=\"Vyman\">Vyman</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Utherydes_Wayn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>See the <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest/Calculations_Ages_(Continued3)#Utherydes_Wayn\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest/Calculations Ages (Continued3)\">Utherydes Wayn</a> calculation.</i></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rawoiafutherydes_wayn.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rawoiafutherydes_wayn.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A World of Ice and Fire\">George R. R. Martin's A World of Ice and Fire</a></i>, Utherydes Wayn.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragotappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragotappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Appendix\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Appendix\">Appendix</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">4.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\">4.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\">4.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-3\">4.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"r